Package it.polimi.ingsw.messages.GameToPlayerMessages.Notify

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    EndOfGameMessage
    This type of message is used by the model to communicate to the virtualView the winner, so that he can close everyone's connection
    ErrorMessageNotification
    This type of message is used by the model to communicate to the virtualView that the player made an error.
    GameStartMessage
    This type of message is used by the model to communicate to the virtualView, which then forwards it to client, that the game can start.
    InfoMessageNotification
    This type of message is used by the model to communicate to the virtualView an information, which has to be sent to the player It contains the message string
    LoseMessage
    This type of message is used by the model to communicate to the virtualView that the specified player lost
    NewBoardStateMessage
    This type of message is used by the model to communicate to the virtualView, which then forwards it to client, the new gameboard state.
    NewTurnMessage
    This type of message is used by the model to communicate to the virtualView which players must now play, after the previous turn ended
    NotifyMessages
    This class's objects are the ones that can be notified by the model to the VirtualView (model's observer) Every type of message which needs to be notified from the model to the Virtual View extends this class
    PositionRequestNotification
    This type of message is used by the model to communicate to the virtualView that the player has to select his starting position
    PossibleCardsNotification
    This type of message is used by the model to communicate to the virtualView that the player must choose his cards
    WinMessage
    This type of message is used by the model to communicate to the virtualView which player won
